
--------------------------------

This tool is used to automatically generate and optimize code for the
Fast Multipole Method (FMM) operators.

The current version (1.0) supports the Cartesian basis set and the 1/r harmonic potential.


Feedback and improvements are welcome.

Please report bugs to Jonathan Coles <jonathan.coles@tum.de>


Usage
-----

To set the parameters for the output, edit the source code.
Set the kind of output desired and the output directory.
Specify a list of expansion orders.

Set the operator variant desired.

Create the output directory.

Run the generator with the command

    python mosaic.py



Requirements
------------

Version 1.0 has been tested with Python 2.7.13 and Sympy 1.1.1.

